Vercel Web Analytics Installation - Implementation Report
==========================================================

Successfully installed and configured Vercel Web Analytics for the Next.js App Router project.

## Changes Made

### 1. Package Installation
- Installed `@vercel/analytics` package using npm
- Added dependency to package.json (version managed by npm)
- Updated package-lock.json with new dependency tree (345 packages added)

### 2. Analytics Component Integration
Modified: `app/layout.tsx`
- Added import statement: `import { Analytics } from '@vercel/analytics/next';`
- Added `<Analytics />` component at the end of the `<body>` tag, after the footer
- Followed Next.js App Router pattern as specified in official Vercel documentation

### 3. Implementation Details
The Analytics component was placed:
- Inside the root layout component (RootLayout)
- At the bottom of the <body> element, ensuring it loads after all page content
- Following the exact pattern from Vercel's official documentation (fetched from https://vercel.com/docs/analytics/quickstart)

